Yes, I'm...

1029
01:09:13,594 --> 01:09:14,844
I'm sorry.

1030
01:09:40,411 --> 01:09:42,039
Hel-- Hello?

1031
01:10:09,316 --> 01:10:10,609
<i>Father Gordon?</i>

1032
01:10:11,068 --> 01:10:13,402
- Judy?
-  <i>You can go now.</i>

1033
01:10:55,487 --> 01:10:57,739
I am protected by God Almighty,

1034
01:10:59,408 --> 01:11:03,786
maker of heaven and Earth,
of all that is seen and unseen.

1035
01:11:05,706 --> 01:11:07,374
My faith is my armor.

1036
01:11:07,749 --> 01:11:09,042
God's light...

1037
01:11:11,253 --> 01:11:13,463
God protect me!

1038
01:11:40,532 --> 01:11:41,575
There she is!

1039
01:11:42,159 --> 01:11:44,994
See, you've always gotta check
if she's got a spark.

1040
01:11:44,995 --> 01:11:46,663
Ah.

1041
01:11:48,457 --> 01:11:51,751
Kept thinking it was the carburetor.
Should have checked the spark plug.

1042
01:11:53,921 --> 01:11:55,129
Nice work.

1043
01:11:55,130 --> 01:11:56,506
Well, you know, I, uh,

1044
01:11:56,507 --> 01:11:59,426
I couldn't afford a mechanic in college,
so I had to teach myself.

1045
01:12:02,429 --> 01:12:04,973
Hey, how much has Judy told you
about what we do?

1046
01:12:06,558 --> 01:12:08,727
Enough to not ask many questions.

1047
01:12:11,855 --> 01:12:14,274
Come inside. I wanna show you something.

1048
01:12:17,861 --> 01:12:19,363
Don't touch anything.

1049
01:12:21,156 --> 01:12:25,118
Everything you see in here
is either haunted, cursed,

1050
01:12:25,119 --> 01:12:28,163
or been used in some
sort of ritualistic practice.

1051
01:12:30,249 --> 01:12:31,625
Nothing's a toy.

1052
01:12:32,918 --> 01:12:34,252
Not even the toys.

1053
01:12:38,966 --> 01:12:40,968
If all these things are so evil,

1054
01:12:41,844 --> 01:12:43,594
why do you keep them around?

1055
01:12:43,595 --> 01:12:45,388
Why not just destroy them?

1056
01:12:45,389 --> 01:12:48,934
It's complicated.
Sometimes that makes things worse.

1057
01:12:49,476 --> 01:12:52,771
Sometimes... they just won't let you.

1058
01:12:53,981 --> 01:12:56,483
We've found it safer
to keep the genie in the bottle.

1059
01:12:57,609 --> 01:12:59,361
It's better in here than out there.

1060
01:13:00,362 --> 01:13:01,737
How many cases you guys had?

1061
01:13:01,738 --> 01:13:03,490
Cases? Oh.

1062
01:13:04,491 --> 01:13:05,659
Maybe a thousand?

1063
01:13:06,243 --> 01:13:07,243
A thousand?

1064
01:13:07,244 --> 01:13:11,206
Yeah, well. We started young,
about your age.

1065
01:13:13,667 --> 01:13:16,253
Mmm. It's funny. This room,

1066
01:13:17,671 --> 01:13:19,506
every little thing in it...

1067
01:13:21,091 --> 01:13:22,593
...is our story.

1068
01:13:25,512 --> 01:13:27,181
It's our life's work.

1069
01:13:29,349 --> 01:13:31,852
Listen, the other day?

1070
01:13:32,895 --> 01:13:33,978
I get it.

1071
01:13:33,979 --> 01:13:38,941
Yeah I-- I was just... nervous,
and you're kinda intimidating.

1072
01:13:38,942 --> 01:13:40,652
We almost lost Judy.

1073
01:13:43,155 --> 01:13:44,615
She was stillborn.

1074
01:13:48,327 --> 01:13:49,787
For probably a minute.

1075
01:13:53,207 --> 01:13:55,709
It was the longest minute of our lives.

1076
01:13:57,878 --> 01:14:01,423
And as a parent,
that's something you never forget.

1077
01:14:05,010 --> 01:14:06,845
So, while I know she's your fiancée,

1078
01:14:09,515 --> 01:14:10,641
for us,

1079
01:14:11,350 --> 01:14:15,896
she will always be that little baby,
fighting for her life.

1080
01:14:18,649 --> 01:14:20,067
I understand, sir.

1081
01:14:23,112 --> 01:14:24,321
Do you?

1082
01:14:29,952 --> 01:14:32,204
What's wrong?

1083
01:14:33,205 --> 01:14:35,124
What?

1084
01:14:35,958 --> 01:14:39,920
Father Gordon, he was a good man.

1085
01:14:41,672 --> 01:14:43,090
A man of God.

1086
01:14:44,508 --> 01:14:46,677
And he helped so many people.

1087
01:14:47,427 --> 01:14:50,556
I didn't know Father
to be a man of despair.

1088
01:14:51,348 --> 01:14:54,643
No, Father Gordon was light.

1089
01:14:56,979 --> 01:15:00,231
And he brought that light
to me and my family,

1090
01:15:00,232 --> 01:15:02,776
when we needed him most.

1091
01:15:07,573 --> 01:15:10,158
I only wish that...

1092
01:15:10,159 --> 01:15:12,327
...we could've done the same for him.

1093
01:16:22,648 --> 01:16:25,484
Mr. Warren? Mrs. Warren?

1094
01:16:26,068 --> 01:16:27,069
Yes?

1095
01:16:27,986 --> 01:16:31,323
I'm sorry, we never met.
My name is Father Ziegler.

1096
01:16:32,449 --> 01:16:37,037
You're actually both a bit infamous
within certain circles of the church.

1097
01:16:37,579 --> 01:16:39,247
Yes, we're aware.

1098
01:16:39,248 --> 01:16:41,624
But Gordon always spoke highly of you.

1099
01:16:41,625 --> 01:16:45,294
He believed in the mission.
And the things you did together.

1100
01:16:45,295 --> 01:16:47,296
He considered you both friends.

1101
01:16:47,297 --> 01:16:48,507
Thank you, Father.

1102
01:16:54,179 --> 01:16:56,181
Excuse me, Father.

1103
01:16:56,807 --> 01:16:57,807
Yes?

1104
01:16:57,808 --> 01:16:59,393
Mm.

1105
01:17:00,185 --> 01:17:01,603
Where was it?

1106
01:17:02,396 --> 01:17:04,690
Where did he die?

1107
01:17:05,858 --> 01:17:07,192
Pennsylvania.

1108
01:17:08,277 --> 01:17:10,362
God only knows why he was out there.

1109
01:17:49,651 --> 01:17:50,360
What?

1110
01:18:18,722 --> 01:18:24,561
<i>♪ Lucy Locket lost her pocket ♪</i>

1111
01:18:25,813 --> 01:18:31,068
<i>♪ Kitty Fisher found it ♪</i>

1112
01:18:52,381 --> 01:18:54,257
Lorraine. What? What's wrong?

1113
01:18:57,761 --> 01:18:59,554
It's Judy.

1114
01:18:59,555 --> 01:19:01,306
There's something wrong with Judy.

1115
01:19:09,940 --> 01:19:11,692
Where is she?

1116
01:19:35,090 --> 01:19:36,508
Oh, boy.

1117
01:19:40,471 --> 01:19:42,264
Ma'am,
can I ask you a few questions?

1118
01:19:47,186 --> 01:19:50,314
{\an8}Hey, stay back from here, okay?

1119
01:19:51,190 --> 01:19:52,774
Whatever is going on in that house,

1120
01:19:52,775 --> 01:19:55,736
we are getting Judy,
and we are taking her home.

1121
01:19:58,322 --> 01:20:00,240
{\an8} All right. Excuse us.

1122
01:20:01,033 --> 01:20:02,366
Sorry. Excuse us.

1123
01:20:05,662 --> 01:20:08,247
It's Ed and Lorraine Warren.
Mrs. Warren, what are you doing here?

1124
01:20:08,248 --> 01:20:10,041
Mrs. Warren, have you been called in
for reinforcements?

1125
01:20:10,042 --> 01:20:11,125
What's in the house?

1126
01:20:11,126 --> 01:20:14,086
Mr. Warren, will you
be performing an exorcism today?

1127
01:20:14,087 --> 01:20:14,962
Excuse me.

1128
01:20:14,963 --> 01:20:15,963
Are the Smurls hiding something?

1129
01:20:15,964 --> 01:20:17,965
- Do you know the Smurls?
-  Ed and Lorraine!

1130
01:20:17,966 --> 01:20:19,258
Are you coming out
of retirement?

1131
01:20:20,177 --> 01:20:20,927
Sir?

1132
01:20:20,928 --> 01:20:22,345
- Sir, can you tell us your name?
-  Hey, just back off.

1133
01:20:22,346 --> 01:20:24,472
What's your connection
to the Warrens, sir?

1134
01:20:24,473 --> 01:20:25,973
Ed and Lorraine...

1135
01:20:27,309 --> 01:20:29,520
You okay?

1136
01:20:31,438 --> 01:20:33,106
Mr. Smurl?

1137
01:20:34,066 --> 01:20:35,191
Ed Warren.

1138
01:20:35,192 --> 01:20:36,734
Uh, yeah. This is my wife.

1139
01:20:36,735 --> 01:20:39,822
Lorraine. Yes, yes!
Please, come in. Please.

1140
01:20:40,656 --> 01:20:42,365
Oh, thank you so much for coming.

1141
01:20:42,366 --> 01:20:45,118
We hear you're the experts.

1142
01:20:45,119 --> 01:20:47,162
People told us you were retired.

1143
01:20:48,831 --> 01:20:49,873
Well.

1144
01:20:54,378 --> 01:20:57,840
<i>I'm so sorry.
We're looking for our daughter.</i>

1145
01:20:58,382 --> 01:20:59,674
Mom?

1146
01:20:59,675 --> 01:21:00,759
Mom?

1147
01:21:01,426 --> 01:21:04,595
Judy!

1148
01:21:04,596 --> 01:21:06,849
That is Janet a-and Jack Smurl.

1149
01:21:07,432 --> 01:21:09,143
Thank God you're safe.

1150
01:21:10,686 --> 01:21:12,979
What are you doing out here?
This is not like you.

1151
01:21:12,980 --> 01:21:16,190
Father Gordon was here.
He came here just before he died.

1152
01:21:16,191 --> 01:21:18,484
I put two and two together,
and I found them.

1153
01:21:18,485 --> 01:21:20,695
- It's been going on for months.
- We need to go.

1154
01:21:20,696 --> 01:21:23,156
What? No. Mom. Mom.

1155
01:21:23,157 --> 01:21:25,116
I'm so sorry. Ed, we need to go.

1156
01:21:25,117 --> 01:21:26,534
- You're leaving?
- Yes, we're leaving.

1157
01:21:26,535 --> 01:21:27,535
Wait, what?

1158
01:21:27,536 --> 01:21:28,870
Really sorry if we've intruded.

1159
01:21:28,871 --> 01:21:30,246
- We can't leave!
- We can't stay.

1160
01:21:30,247 --> 01:21:31,372
- We can talk about this outside.
- Mom!

1161
01:21:31,373 --> 01:21:32,457
It's been a long drive.

1162
01:21:32,458 --> 01:21:34,292
Again, we're really sorry. Come on, Judy.

1163
01:21:34,293 --> 01:21:36,295
-  Say something.
- Stop!

1164
01:21:42,509 --> 01:21:46,096
We don't run from fights, right?

1165
01:21:47,848 --> 01:21:49,599
I mean, that's what
you'd always tell each other,

1166
01:21:49,600 --> 01:21:51,894
when there was a family
that needed you.

1167
01:21:54,730 --> 01:21:58,442
As a kid, I didn't understand
why you had to leave.

1168
01:21:59,318 --> 01:22:02,696
Why you gave so much of yourselves
to people you didn't know.

1169
01:22:04,239 --> 01:22:06,033
And even now, I don't know.

1170
01:22:08,494 --> 01:22:11,580
I don't know why I'm here, I really don't.

1171
01:22:12,456 --> 01:22:14,208
But we're all here now.

1172
01:22:15,584 --> 01:22:18,253
And they need us.

1173
01:22:29,765 --> 01:22:31,642
They need you.

1174
01:23:05,134 --> 01:23:06,050
Any comments for us?

1175
01:23:06,051 --> 01:23:08,679
Mr. Warren, do
you think it's a real haunting?

1176
01:23:11,557 --> 01:23:13,641
We should have never gone to the press.

1177
01:23:13,642 --> 01:23:16,144
Now our neighbors can't stand us.

1178
01:23:16,145 --> 01:23:18,021
They think we wanted this.

1179
01:23:18,814 --> 01:23:21,107
I didn't know
it was gonna turn into a circus.

1180
01:23:21,108 --> 01:23:23,609
We wanted someone like you, experts.

1181
01:23:23,610 --> 01:23:25,069
People who've dealt with this before.

1182
01:23:25,070 --> 01:23:28,364
L-Let's... take this back
to the beginning. When did it start?

1183
01:23:28,365 --> 01:23:31,033
- Uh, Heather's confirmation.
- Yeah.

1184
01:23:31,034 --> 01:23:33,120
What do you mean, you saw him die?

1185
01:23:35,914 --> 01:23:37,248
I mean, were you here?

1186
01:23:37,249 --> 01:23:40,251
No, back home. In a vision.

1187
01:23:40,252 --> 01:23:42,795
But... it was different.

1188
01:23:42,796 --> 01:23:43,880
Did you tell your mom?

1189
01:23:43,881 --> 01:23:47,509
No. I can't talk to her anymore.
She's always so...

1190
01:23:48,260 --> 01:23:50,179
- Worried.
- Yeah.

1191
01:23:51,346 --> 01:23:52,764
There's something else.

1192
01:23:53,265 --> 01:23:56,185
I don't know how to say it,
but it's like...

1193
01:23:57,895 --> 01:24:02,649
...something wants me to be here.

1194
01:24:04,193 --> 01:24:07,028
So your parents were living here?

1195
01:24:07,029 --> 01:24:08,781
Which one of you? Which parents?

1196
01:24:09,615 --> 01:24:13,118
Yeah, they've been with us all along,
since we moved in, and um...

1197
01:25:38,871 --> 01:25:40,873
He started making pancakes.

1198
01:25:46,170 --> 01:25:49,256
So, is this, like, a normal case?

1199
01:25:50,257 --> 01:25:52,468
They're never normal.

1200
01:25:53,093 --> 01:25:56,220
No, I mean, do you always cook pancakes?

1201
01:25:56,221 --> 01:25:58,682
Is that part of the process?

1202
01:26:06,023 --> 01:26:07,608
Sometimes it's waffles.

1203
01:26:12,988 --> 01:26:15,240
No, every case is different.

1204
01:26:15,824 --> 01:26:17,159
Every family's different.

1205
01:26:18,118 --> 01:26:21,455
One thing that's always the same
is the fear.

1206
01:26:22,289 --> 01:26:23,957
You can see it in their eyes.

1207
01:26:25,292 --> 01:26:27,169
And a demon will prey on that.

1208
01:26:27,878 --> 01:26:30,463
It'll try to isolate them,
use their fears against them.

1209
01:26:30,464 --> 01:26:32,633
So part of the job is just...

1210
01:26:34,051 --> 01:26:35,844
letting them know they're not alone.

1211
01:26:37,137 --> 01:26:38,180
Right.

1212
01:26:42,684 --> 01:26:44,311
Judy told me you were a cop.

1213
01:26:45,229 --> 01:26:47,230
What happened? Why'd you quit?

1214
01:26:47,231 --> 01:26:48,315
It's nothing.

1215
01:26:56,240 --> 01:26:58,283
Okay, so...

1216
01:26:59,451 --> 01:27:00,452
I was working in Bloomfield.

1217
01:27:01,662 --> 01:27:04,164
You know, small town.
Nothing ever happens.

1218
01:27:04,790 --> 01:27:07,584
Me and my partner,
we get a domestic violence call.

1219
01:27:09,002 --> 01:27:13,381
And we pull up to the house,
and we hear fighting inside.

1220
01:27:13,382 --> 01:27:15,884
So, I knock on the door.

1221
01:27:16,718 --> 01:27:17,969
And immediately,

1222
01:27:17,970 --> 01:27:20,096
the door flies open,

1223
01:27:20,097 --> 01:27:23,517
and this guy shoves
a twelve-gauge shotgun right in my face.

1224
01:27:24,893 --> 01:27:27,271
And I hear... click.

1225
01:27:28,438 --> 01:27:29,773
I, uh...

1226
01:27:30,274 --> 01:27:33,861
I unfreeze,
and, uh, we take the guy down.

1227
01:27:34,319 --> 01:27:35,529
Arrest him.

1228
01:27:37,573 --> 01:27:40,199
Later, my partner comes up to me,

1229
01:27:40,200 --> 01:27:43,203
and he says, "You're a dead man."

1230
01:27:44,955 --> 01:27:46,290
He shows me the shotgun.

1231
01:27:48,167 --> 01:27:49,126
It was loaded.

1232
01:27:50,461 --> 01:27:52,336
Primer was struck on the shell.

1233
01:27:52,337 --> 01:27:53,589
Misfire.

1234
01:27:55,757 --> 01:27:59,511
I figure, there's a world where I'm dead.

1235
01:28:01,054 --> 01:28:03,557
Where I never grow old.

1236
01:28:04,475 --> 01:28:06,268
I never have kids.

1237
01:28:06,894 --> 01:28:08,937
I never get to marry your daughter.

1238
01:28:14,610 --> 01:28:17,571
So next day, I-I quit,

1239
01:28:18,155 --> 01:28:20,741
and I go out and buy that ring for Judy.

1240
01:28:32,878 --> 01:28:35,755
<i>- This is my wastepaper basket, Bert.
- Of course, it's your waste basket!</i>

1241
01:28:35,756 --> 01:28:37,548
<i>- Oh, yeah.
- You put it on my head!</i>

1242
01:28:37,549 --> 01:28:39,467
<i>- Thank you, Bert.
- "Thank you?"</i>

1243
01:28:39,468 --> 01:28:40,551
<i>That's my wastepaper basket</i>

1244
01:28:40,552 --> 01:28:42,512
<i>for throwing stuff in
when I make a mistake.</i>

1245
01:28:42,513 --> 01:28:45,056
<i>Terrific. Okay, now, Ernie, Ernie...</i>

1246
01:28:47,059 --> 01:28:49,352
Should we do a silly face? Yeah?

1247
01:29:04,159 --> 01:29:06,494
Sorry, the flash was supposed to be off.

1248
01:29:09,790 --> 01:29:11,416
I just thought I could...

1249
01:29:13,252 --> 01:29:14,670
...document it all.

1250
01:29:19,091 --> 01:29:20,175
Everything okay?

1251
01:29:21,844 --> 01:29:22,927
Yeah.

1252
01:29:30,519 --> 01:29:34,231
I just realized,
I've never seen you guys at work.

1253
01:29:46,368 --> 01:29:47,744
I feel it, too.

1254
01:29:56,670 --> 01:29:58,296
Stay here.

1255
01:29:58,297 --> 01:30:01,049
- Mom, I can help.
- Judy, you promised.

1256
01:30:18,525 --> 01:30:19,943
<i>Mommy, Mommy!</i>

1257
01:30:26,617 --> 01:30:28,035
<i>Mommy, Mommy!</i>

1258
01:30:34,625 --> 01:30:36,043
<i>Mommy, Mommy!</i>

1259
01:30:43,675 --> 01:30:44,676
<i>Mommy--</i>

1260
01:30:51,475 --> 01:30:53,309
Hey, Carin.

1261
01:30:53,310 --> 01:30:54,393
Sorry.

1262
01:30:54,394 --> 01:30:55,395
It's okay.

1263
01:30:56,605 --> 01:30:58,232
Uh, what's her name?

1264
01:30:58,816 --> 01:30:59,942
This is Susie.

1265
01:31:00,734 --> 01:31:02,027
Hey, Susie.

1266
01:31:03,278 --> 01:31:04,863
Do you like dolls?

1267
01:31:05,489 --> 01:31:06,865
Uh...

1268
01:31:08,242 --> 01:31:09,409
Not really.

1269
01:32:38,290 --> 01:32:39,290
<i>Get away from her!</i>

1270
01:32:39,291 --> 01:32:42,376
<i>I know what you did.</i>

1271
01:32:42,377 --> 01:32:43,920
<i>You dirty girl!</i>

1272
01:32:43,921 --> 01:32:45,923
<i>You filthy girl!</i>

1273
01:32:48,425 --> 01:32:49,760
<i>No!</i>

1274
01:33:05,067 --> 01:33:07,444
The spirits, there are three of them.

1275
01:33:08,570 --> 01:33:11,865
They never lived in this house,
but on this land.

1276
01:33:13,826 --> 01:33:15,369
This was farmland.

1277
01:33:18,914 --> 01:33:20,124
Uh...

1278
01:33:22,167 --> 01:33:23,836
There was a woman.

1279
01:33:24,711 --> 01:33:26,964
She was wild. She...

1280
01:33:28,257 --> 01:33:29,967
Just so tormented.

1281
01:33:30,759 --> 01:33:33,345
She had an affair, and...

1282
01:33:34,596 --> 01:33:37,141
...her husband went insane.

1283
01:33:38,183 --> 01:33:41,227
He took an axe, and he went after her.

1284
01:33:41,228 --> 01:33:45,022
She hid in the basement,
but she wasn't alone.

1285
01:33:45,023 --> 01:33:47,484
She went with her elderly mother.

1286
01:33:49,903 --> 01:33:52,697
- And he killed them both.
- Look, we've seen

1287
01:33:52,698 --> 01:33:54,949
violent manifestations like that before.

1288
01:33:54,950 --> 01:33:56,617
So why is this different?

1289
01:33:56,618 --> 01:33:58,912
The three spirits are a façade.

1290
01:33:59,204 --> 01:34:01,874
Something else is blocking my vision.

1291
01:34:02,791 --> 01:34:04,293
Hiding behind them.

1292
01:34:05,210 --> 01:34:06,336
Demonic?

1293
01:34:08,046 --> 01:34:11,716
It's controlling the spirits.
It's using them against the Smurls.

1294
01:34:11,717 --> 01:34:15,762
But what's it want?
I mean, this has been going on for months.

1295
01:34:16,722 --> 01:34:18,182
What's it waiting for?

1296
01:34:24,605 --> 01:34:25,439
Judy!

1297
01:34:28,025 --> 01:34:29,192
Mom?

1298
01:34:29,193 --> 01:34:30,861
Can you come up here, please?

1299
01:34:53,759 --> 01:34:54,885
Mom?

1300
01:37:06,433 --> 01:37:07,518
Oh.

1301
01:37:28,747 --> 01:37:30,165
Annabelle?

1302
01:37:56,859 --> 01:37:57,776
Judy?

1303
01:38:00,112 --> 01:38:01,113
Are you there?

1304
01:38:02,072 --> 01:38:03,157
Carin?

1305
01:39:15,437 --> 01:39:16,897
-  Judy!
-  Judy!

1306
01:39:19,274 --> 01:39:20,650
Your head!

1307
01:39:20,651 --> 01:39:22,778
What happened?

1308
01:39:28,575 --> 01:39:30,202
There's something in the attic.

1309
01:39:39,419 --> 01:39:40,838
It can't be.

1310
01:39:41,672 --> 01:39:45,884
It... found us.

1311
01:39:51,974 --> 01:39:53,142
Lorraine?

1312
01:39:58,897 --> 01:40:01,108
No, Lorraine. No, don't.

1313
01:40:15,205 --> 01:40:18,375
Ed, something's changed.

1314
01:40:20,919 --> 01:40:22,880
Something's different.

1315
01:40:30,220 --> 01:40:33,307
<i>Then, after about a week,
Judy recovered.</i>

1316
01:40:33,724 --> 01:40:36,143
The doctors said
they'd never seen anything like it.

1317
01:40:37,269 --> 01:40:39,021
She was a miracle.

1318
01:40:40,397 --> 01:40:43,776
But as for that mirror,
we never saw it again...

1319
01:40:45,778 --> 01:40:47,070
...until today.

1320
01:40:48,197 --> 01:40:51,532
<i>But I don't understand.
Heather and I threw that thing away.</i>

1321
01:40:51,533 --> 01:40:54,745
<i>With these things,
it's never that simple.</i>

1322
01:40:55,871 --> 01:41:00,125
<i>It wasn't done with you,
and it wasn't done with us.</i>

1323
01:41:02,920 --> 01:41:04,755
Okay, so then what happened to the woman

1324
01:41:05,839 --> 01:41:07,674
from the antique store?

1325
01:41:11,261 --> 01:41:12,221
We don't know.

1326
01:41:12,596 --> 01:41:13,806
Uh...

1327
01:41:15,015 --> 01:41:16,225
We never went back.

1328
01:41:17,226 --> 01:41:20,312
That thing in your attic is a demon.

1329
01:41:20,646 --> 01:41:22,856
It's the first one
that we ever encountered.

1330
01:41:24,066 --> 01:41:28,612
We were young, and we were scared,
and we almost lost our daughter.

1331
01:41:29,947 --> 01:41:32,949
So, we told ourselves that
the risk was just too great,

1332
01:41:32,950 --> 01:41:35,160
so we couldn't chance going back.

1333
01:41:36,620 --> 01:41:38,038
So, yes.

1334
01:41:39,998 --> 01:41:41,208
We ran away.

1335
01:41:44,920 --> 01:41:45,838
I'll...

1336
01:41:46,922 --> 01:41:49,590
...take it as a good sign
you're still here.

1337
01:41:49,591 --> 01:41:51,008
Mm.

1338
01:41:51,009 --> 01:41:52,261
We're not leaving you.

1339
01:42:01,019 --> 01:42:01,937
Some water?

1340
01:42:02,437 --> 01:42:03,564
Sorry.

1341
01:42:04,439 --> 01:42:05,274
So, what now?

1342
01:42:06,650 --> 01:42:07,943
How do you get rid of it?

1343
01:42:09,611 --> 01:42:12,738
Ed! You're really
gonna take that thing home?

1344
01:42:12,739 --> 01:42:14,323
We can't leave it here.

1345
01:42:14,324 --> 01:42:16,869
Artifact room is the only place
that can contain it.

1346
01:42:20,747 --> 01:42:24,834
All right, West Pittston,
back home to Monroe. Take 80.

1347
01:42:24,835 --> 01:42:27,253
Lorraine and Judy can stay behind.
Wait, 84 is faster.

1348
01:42:27,254 --> 01:42:29,173
Eighty is much quicker this time of night.

1349
01:42:31,049 --> 01:42:33,134
Listen to me, whatever happens tonight,

1350
01:42:33,135 --> 01:42:35,220
you have got to do what I say, okay?

1351
01:42:36,263 --> 01:42:37,097
Got it.

1352
01:42:42,811 --> 01:42:44,062
What? What is it?

1353
01:42:48,275 --> 01:42:49,234
It's nothin'.

1354
01:42:50,277 --> 01:42:51,235
Everything okay?

1355
01:42:51,236 --> 01:42:53,363
I-It's just something Lorraine said.

1356
01:42:55,491 --> 01:42:56,992
Something feels different.

1357
01:43:09,838 --> 01:43:12,132
Mom, I'm-- I'm sorry.

1358
01:43:12,591 --> 01:43:14,218
No, I'm sorry.

1359
01:43:15,093 --> 01:43:17,304
I should have never let you stay.

1360
01:43:22,643 --> 01:43:25,229
Once we start, there's no going back.

1361
01:43:26,563 --> 01:43:27,689
Don't look at it.

1362
01:43:29,149 --> 01:43:31,693
And don't touch it directly.

1363
01:43:32,444 --> 01:43:33,862
Just keep your gloves on.

1364
01:43:34,488 --> 01:43:35,697
Anything can happen.

1365
01:43:37,199 --> 01:43:39,075
And most likely, anything will.

1366
01:43:45,165 --> 01:43:46,667
"St. Michael the Archangel,

1367
01:43:47,668 --> 01:43:49,294
defend us in the day of battle.

1368
01:43:50,420 --> 01:43:53,464
<i>Be our safeguard against the wickedness
and snares of the devil."</i>

1369
01:43:55,759 --> 01:43:56,969
<i>"May God rebuke him.</i>

1370
01:43:57,970 --> 01:44:01,222
<i>And by the power of God,
cast into hell, Satan,</i>

1371
01:44:01,223 --> 01:44:04,434
<i>and all other evil spirits
who prowl through the world,</i>

1372
01:44:05,018 --> 01:44:06,686
<i>seeking the ruin of souls."</i>

1373
01:44:08,397 --> 01:44:09,647
<i>"Amen."</i>

1374
01:44:10,941 --> 01:44:12,108
- I'll get the car ready.
- Yeah.

1375
01:44:12,109 --> 01:44:13,444
We'll be down in a second.
All right.

1376
01:44:16,655 --> 01:44:17,530
-  You ready?
- Yeah.

1377
01:44:17,531 --> 01:44:19,240
Two, three... Yeah.

1378
01:44:20,659 --> 01:44:22,243
-  Come on, Simon!
-  Let's go, Simon!

1379
01:44:22,244 --> 01:44:23,453
Come on, Simon!

1380
01:44:23,454 --> 01:44:25,121
- Come on! Be a good boy.
- Come on!

1381
01:44:25,122 --> 01:44:26,956
Girls, get him outta here.

1382
01:44:26,957 --> 01:44:28,083
We're trying!

1383
01:44:29,376 --> 01:44:31,962
So, is it just drywall
underneath the insulation?

1384
01:44:32,421 --> 01:44:33,088
Yeah.

1385
01:44:33,672 --> 01:44:35,131
So, if we step off these boards,

1386
01:44:35,132 --> 01:44:36,717
- we're going--
- Straight through the ceiling.

1387
01:44:37,176 --> 01:44:38,384
Don't wanna make it too easy.

1388
01:44:47,060 --> 01:44:48,270
Is it just me or...

1389
01:44:49,480 --> 01:44:51,148
or does it feel like it's getting heavier?

1390
01:44:51,648 --> 01:44:53,567
It is.
Sometimes these things can be...

1391
01:44:54,359 --> 01:44:55,235
...stubborn.

1392
01:44:55,736 --> 01:44:56,528
Oh!

1393
01:44:57,571 --> 01:44:58,238
You okay?

1394
01:45:00,115 --> 01:45:01,158
- Yeah, I'm good.
- Okay.

1395
01:45:04,286 --> 01:45:05,245
Ed...

1396
01:45:06,663 --> 01:45:07,331
Look.

1397
01:45:11,543 --> 01:45:12,502
Keep moving.

1398
01:45:19,551 --> 01:45:20,468
Come on!

1399
01:45:22,513 --> 01:45:25,516
Judy... Judy, what's wrong?

1400
01:45:31,605 --> 01:45:32,438
Mom.

1401
01:45:36,318 --> 01:45:37,820
I don't feel good.

1402
01:45:41,532 --> 01:45:42,532
We're almost there.

1403
01:45:50,791 --> 01:45:52,333
Don't look at it!

1404
01:45:52,334 --> 01:45:54,419
Don't-- don't look at it!

1405
01:45:54,920 --> 01:45:56,045
She's with us!

1406
01:45:56,046 --> 01:45:57,047
Jack, it's just us.

1407
01:45:57,381 --> 01:45:58,881
She's here! I saw her, Ed.

1408
01:45:58,882 --> 01:46:00,216
- I saw her.
- No, it's just us.

1409
01:46:00,217 --> 01:46:02,426
- She is here.
- Jack.

1410
01:46:02,427 --> 01:46:04,388
- Focus on what you're doing.
- I saw her. She's here.

1411
01:46:04,680 --> 01:46:05,805
Jack, watch where you're going.

1412
01:46:07,307 --> 01:46:08,684
Oh!

1413
01:46:10,769 --> 01:46:12,855
Jack, get outta the way! No!

1414
01:46:14,898 --> 01:46:16,274
Daddy!

1415
01:46:16,275 --> 01:46:18,776
Stay right here.

1416
01:46:18,777 --> 01:46:19,945
Mommy!

1417
01:46:20,237 --> 01:46:22,280
Ed? What's going on?

1418
01:46:22,281 --> 01:46:23,656
Jack! What happened?

1419
01:46:23,657 --> 01:46:25,659
Get back!

1420
01:46:25,951 --> 01:46:26,909
No, get back!

1421
01:46:26,910 --> 01:46:28,412
Just keep everybody away.

1422
01:46:29,830 --> 01:46:31,622
- Let me go get Tony.
- No, I can do this.

1423
01:46:31,623 --> 01:46:32,958
Just help me up.

1424
01:46:34,918 --> 01:46:37,337
Lorraine, stay down there!
Keep everybody down there.

1425
01:46:43,760 --> 01:46:45,929
Come on. Come on.

1426
01:46:47,723 --> 01:46:48,932
Yes!

1427
01:47:04,490 --> 01:47:05,449
What the--

1428
01:47:10,662 --> 01:47:12,664
Oh, man. Oh, God.

1429
01:47:14,583 --> 01:47:15,876
My God.

1430
01:47:19,588 --> 01:47:20,422
What?

1431
01:48:35,414 --> 01:48:36,372
No.

1432
01:48:41,545 --> 01:48:43,547
<i>♪ Lucy Locket ♪</i>

1433
01:48:44,465 --> 01:48:46,717
<i>♪ Lost her pocket ♪</i>

1434
01:48:47,468 --> 01:48:50,929
<i>♪ Kitty Fisher found it ♪</i>

1435
01:48:52,973 --> 01:48:58,145
<i>♪ Not a penny was there in it ♪</i>

1436
01:49:00,689 --> 01:49:05,402
<i>♪ Only ribbon 'round it ♪</i>

1437
01:49:07,279 --> 01:49:08,572
Mommy?

1438
01:49:09,990 --> 01:49:11,991
I don't feel so good.

1439
01:49:13,494 --> 01:49:14,495
Judy?

1440
01:49:16,079 --> 01:49:19,999
We've been waiting so patiently

1441
01:49:20,000 --> 01:49:23,962
for little Judy to come back to us.

1442
01:49:34,097 --> 01:49:35,973
-  It's okay.
-  I'm sorry, Ed.

1443
01:49:41,313 --> 01:49:42,648
Okay. It's okay.

1444
01:49:43,649 --> 01:49:44,524
Easy, easy, easy.

1445
01:49:46,693 --> 01:49:48,654
Simon, get back.

1446
01:49:54,368 --> 01:49:55,077
Judy?

1447
01:49:55,536 --> 01:49:56,745
Simon, come back.

1448
01:49:58,372 --> 01:49:59,289
What's going on?

1449
01:49:59,957 --> 01:50:01,166
Girls, come.

1450
01:50:01,750 --> 01:50:02,751
Pull him, Heather!

1451
01:50:04,294 --> 01:50:05,795
Mommy?

1452
01:50:06,839 --> 01:50:08,006
No! No!

1453
01:50:08,715 --> 01:50:09,675
-  Mommy!
- Hey!

1454
01:50:16,765 --> 01:50:18,474
- It's okay.
-  Simon!

1455
01:50:18,475 --> 01:50:19,684
- Oh, no!
-  Let me in!

1456
01:50:19,685 --> 01:50:21,103
-  Stop! No!
-  No!

1457
01:50:21,645 --> 01:50:23,814
-  Simon!
- No! You get away from them!

1458
01:50:24,148 --> 01:50:25,314
You get away from them!

1459
01:50:25,315 --> 01:50:26,150
Judy.

1460
01:50:28,861 --> 01:50:30,445
No. No!

1461
01:50:30,446 --> 01:50:33,240
No, Judy, look at me.
Look in my eyes.

1462
01:50:34,074 --> 01:50:35,199
Daddy?

1463
01:50:35,200 --> 01:50:35,993
Yeah.

1464
01:50:36,785 --> 01:50:38,078
Come on, come on.

1465
01:50:38,412 --> 01:50:39,663
It's-- Judy--

1466
01:50:40,372 --> 01:50:43,124
- Open the door! Open the door!
- Open the door!

1467
01:50:43,125 --> 01:50:45,669
- Open the door!
- It won't open!

1468
01:50:46,336 --> 01:50:49,422
-  <i>♪ Lucy Locket... ♪</i>
- Judy, listen to my voice.

1469
01:50:49,423 --> 01:50:52,509
- I know you're in there. It's Daddy!
<i>- ♪ ...Lost her pocket ♪</i>

1470
01:50:53,177 --> 01:50:57,096
<i>♪ Kitty Fisher found it ♪</i>

1471
01:50:57,097 --> 01:51:00,099
I know you can hear me. Judy, Judy!

1472
01:51:00,100 --> 01:51:02,478
<i>♪ You're not there ♪</i>

1473
01:51:22,039 --> 01:51:22,915
Judy.

1474
01:51:28,796 --> 01:51:31,590
<i>♪ Lucy Locket... ♪</i>

1475
01:51:32,841 --> 01:51:34,301
Mommy!

1476
01:51:35,302 --> 01:51:36,010
No!

1477
01:51:38,597 --> 01:51:40,891
Wait there!
I'm going 'round the back, okay?

1478
01:52:45,205 --> 01:52:46,206
Oh, God.

1479
01:53:15,110 --> 01:53:16,235
Lorraine?

1480
01:53:18,071 --> 01:53:19,447
Hey, you okay?

1481
01:53:19,448 --> 01:53:21,533
Tony.

1482
01:53:28,540 --> 01:53:29,999
- Stay here! Stay here!
- No!

1483
01:53:30,000 --> 01:53:32,210
No, no, Mommy, don't leave us!

1484
01:53:34,379 --> 01:53:36,088
Are you okay?

1485
01:53:36,089 --> 01:53:37,048
What should I do?

1486
01:53:37,049 --> 01:53:38,841
Should I call the police? An ambulance?

1487
01:53:38,842 --> 01:53:40,384
- There's no time.
- Mommy!

1488
01:53:40,385 --> 01:53:41,844
Get Jack and the girls,
and get outta here.

1489
01:53:41,845 --> 01:53:42,595
Jack?

1490
01:53:42,596 --> 01:53:43,847
She's going up to the attic.

1491
01:53:44,139 --> 01:53:44,890
Go!

1492
01:53:46,141 --> 01:53:48,601
Come on, quickly, girls! Get out!

1493
01:53:48,602 --> 01:53:50,813
-  Let me help you!
-  It's okay. It's okay.

1494
01:53:53,398 --> 01:53:54,774
Ed!

1495
01:53:54,775 --> 01:53:56,318
It wanted Judy.

1496
01:53:56,860 --> 01:53:58,570
It's always been Judy.

1497
01:54:00,405 --> 01:54:01,406
Get the book!

1498
01:54:07,412 --> 01:54:08,412
It's all right.

1499
01:54:26,223 --> 01:54:26,974
Judy!

1500
01:54:29,017 --> 01:54:30,810
No! Judy!

1501
01:54:32,521 --> 01:54:34,815
Ed! The knife! Ed.

1502
01:54:45,659 --> 01:54:46,368
Oh...

1503
01:54:47,369 --> 01:54:48,745
No!

1504
01:54:54,084 --> 01:54:55,334
Ed!

1505
01:54:55,335 --> 01:54:56,627
Get her down!

1506
01:54:56,628 --> 01:54:59,380
-  Tony! Lift her up!
- Get her down! Get her down!

1507
01:54:59,381 --> 01:55:02,551
- Oh, my God! Judy! Judy!
-  Oh, God!

1508
01:55:07,764 --> 01:55:10,725
Oh, my God! Judy!

1509
01:55:12,853 --> 01:55:13,812
Come on!

1510
01:55:21,028 --> 01:55:21,987
Judy!

1511
01:55:37,628 --> 01:55:39,504
Hang on. Okay. Okay.

1512
01:55:43,550 --> 01:55:45,468
- She's not got a pulse.
-  No.

1513
01:55:45,469 --> 01:55:47,428
Get outta the way.
Just get outta the way!

1514
01:55:54,144 --> 01:55:55,687
- Ed, I can help!
- I got it!

1515
01:55:56,271 --> 01:55:58,147
- I've got it!
- Judy...

1516
01:55:58,148 --> 01:56:00,149
- Oh, God! No!
- Come on, baby. Come on, baby, please.

1517
01:56:00,150 --> 01:56:01,818
- Come on, Judy.
- Please, please.

1518
01:56:01,819 --> 01:56:03,986
- No! Oh, my baby! My baby!
- Come on, honey.

1519
01:56:03,987 --> 01:56:05,196
Come on, baby.

1520
01:56:05,197 --> 01:56:06,573
- You can do this.
- Please, Lord!

1521
01:56:07,157 --> 01:56:09,200
Please, don't take her. Please, God.

1522
01:56:09,201 --> 01:56:10,159
Please.

1523
01:56:19,503 --> 01:56:20,504
No...

1524
01:56:24,258 --> 01:56:26,092
- Ed?
- I can't-- Keep going.

1525
01:56:26,093 --> 01:56:27,260
Okay.

1526
01:56:29,721 --> 01:56:31,640
Oh, Father!

1527
01:56:32,224 --> 01:56:33,308
One, two.

1528
01:56:35,102 --> 01:56:36,060
Come on!

1529
01:56:40,149 --> 01:56:41,066
Come on.

1530
01:56:47,197 --> 01:56:48,781
Oh, God!

1531
01:56:48,782 --> 01:56:51,284
Thank you! Thank you, God. Thank you.

1532
01:56:51,285 --> 01:56:52,286
Judy.

1533
01:57:08,177 --> 01:57:09,219
Mom?

1534
01:57:10,304 --> 01:57:11,346
Dad?

1535
01:57:27,404 --> 01:57:28,238
Ed.

1536
01:57:29,531 --> 01:57:30,449
Stop it!

1537
01:57:34,369 --> 01:57:35,871
In the name of the Father,
the Son, and the Holy Spirit.

1538
01:57:36,747 --> 01:57:39,708
<i>In nomine Patris, et Filii,
et Spiritus Sancti.</i>

1539
01:57:43,295 --> 01:57:45,839
We cast you out. Every unclean spirit!

1540
01:57:47,925 --> 01:57:49,675
Every satanic power!

1541
01:57:49,676 --> 01:57:50,719
Every legion!

1542
01:57:51,553 --> 01:57:54,014
And by the power of our Lord Jesus Christ!

1543
01:58:05,359 --> 01:58:06,360
Ed!

1544
01:58:14,993 --> 01:58:17,995
<i>Omnem potentiam satanicam!</i>

1545
01:58:18,997 --> 01:58:22,584
